PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780981448
OL,3,CCancer vaccine developed for people at
OL,4,Chight risk of disease
OL,6,FA study launching this summer will
OL,7,Fassess whether the vaccine can train
OL,8,Fthe immune system to recognise and
OL,9,Feliminate pre-cancerous cells in
OL,10,Fpeople with Lynch syndrome before
OL,11,Fcancer develops.
OL,13,FLynch syndrome is linked to a far
OL,14,Fhigher risk of bowel, womb and ovarian
OL,15,Fcancer, alongside other types such as
OL,16,Fstomach, pancreatic, kidney and skin
OL,17,Fcancer.
OL,19,FAround one in 300 people in England
OL,20,Fhave Lynch syndrome, but just 5% are
OL,21,Faware they have the condition.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780981448
OL,3,CCancer vaccine developed for people at
OL,4,Chight risk of disease
OL,6,FAround 1,100 bowel cancers are caused
OL,7,Fby Lynch syndrome each year in England
OL,8,Fand it is thought the syndrome
OL,9,Fincreases the lifetime risk of
OL,10,Fdeveloping bowel cancer by around 80%.
OL,12,FOnce patients receive the new mRNA-
OL,13,F4194 jab, experts will then analyse
OL,14,Ftheir immune responses, what the
OL,15,Fperfect dose is and will check the jab
OL,16,Fis safe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780981448
OL,3,CCancer vaccine developed for people at
OL,4,Chight risk of disease
OL,6,FProfessor David Church, Cancer
OL,7,FResearch UK senior cancer research
OL,8,Ffellow in the University of Oxford's
OL,9,Fcentre for human genetics and the lead
OL,10,Finvestigator of the trial, said the
OL,11,Faim of the new study is to "train the
OL,12,Fimmune system with a vaccine" to
OL,13,Frecognise abnormalities and stop them
OL,14,Fdeveloping into cancer.
OL,16,FProf Church said the mRNA jab acts as
OL,17,F"an instruction manual" for the body
OL,18,Fto attack the pre-cancerous cells.
OL,26,@sD@\OUtD@]O]yD@AOUyD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780981448
OL,3,CCancer vaccine developed for people at
OL,4,Chight risk of disease
OL,6,FHowever, he said there may be a need
OL,7,Ffor patients to have a booster jab at
OL,8,Fsome stage.
OL,10,FHe said the vaccine could be
OL,11,F"transformative" in preventing cancer
OL,12,Fin people with Lynch syndrome and can
OL,13,Falso be given to Lynch patients who
OL,14,Fhave already suffered one type of
OL,15,Fcancer.
OL,17,FProf Church said results from this
OL,18,Fstudy will give insights "that are
OL,19,Fgeneralisable" which could help aid
OL,20,Fresearch into other types of cancers.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
